AN IDIOT OR A GENIUS!

244
00:13:02,125 --> 00:13:04,125
I LIKE THIS FELLOW!

245
00:13:04,208 --> 00:13:06,500
[LAUGHS]

246
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:08,250
CHESS MASTER HEX.

247
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:10,666
ESTIMATED TO BE 98 YEARS OLD.

248
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:15,041
A PROGRAMMER THAT HAD BEEN
DUBBED A GENIUS FROM HIS TEENS.

249
00:13:15,125 --> 00:13:17,000
IN THE COSMO NET
CHESS TOURNAMENTS,

250
00:13:17,083 --> 00:13:20,041
HE HELD THE CHAMPION
SEAT FOR DECADES.

251
00:13:20,125 --> 00:13:22,958
HE APPLIED HIS INTELLECT TO
THE HYPERSPACE GATE PROJECT,

252
00:13:23,041 --> 00:13:25,250
JOINING THE PROGRAM
AT 30 YEARS OF AGE.

253
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:27,875
HE EVENTUALLY DEVELOPED
THE CENTRAL CONTROL SYSTEM

254
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:29,208
THAT ALL GATES USE TO THIS DAY.

255
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:32,833
BUT AFTER THAT,
HE STARTED TO HAVE DOUBTS.

256
00:13:32,916 --> 00:13:34,958
HE SAID THE DESIGN
HAD DEFECTS

257
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:36,958
AND THE GATES
SHOULDN'T BE BUILT YET.

258
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:38,541
HE WANTED TO RUN MORE TESTS.

259
00:13:38,625 --> 00:13:40,916
SO THEY FIRED HIM AND
BUILT THE GATES ANYWAY.

260
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,625
HE'S BEEN MISSING
FOR THE LAST 50 YEARS.

261
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:46,291
SO HE'S THE MASTERMIND
WHO TAUGHT THOSE BEGINNERS.

262
00:13:46,375 --> 00:13:47,833
BUT WHY?

263
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:50,166
IS HE TRYING TO GET REVENGE
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS OR WHAT?

264
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:54,041
MAYBE IF WE TRACK HIM DOWN,
WE CAN GET TO THE BOTTOM OF IT.

265
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:54,916
HEY, ED?

266
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,333
EDWARD IS VERY BUSY.

267
00:13:56,416 --> 00:13:57,375
TRY LATER.

268
00:13:57,458 --> 00:13:58,250
FORGET LATER.

269
00:13:58,333 --> 00:13:59,583
WE NEED SOME HELP NOW.

270
00:13:59,666 --> 00:14:01,541
GIVE ME THAT

271
00:14:01,625 --> 00:14:02,833
[HISSES]

272
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:05,958
ED, WE'RE TRYING
TO FIND A GUY NAMED HEX.

273
00:14:06,041 --> 00:14:07,208
HE'S IN CYBERSPACE.

274
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:10,208
HEX.
HEX THE CHESS MASTER.

275
00:14:10,291 --> 00:14:13,791
EDWARD IS PLAYING CHESS
AGAINST HIM RIGHT NOW.

276
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:15,708
HUH?

277
00:14:27,083 --> 00:14:28,791
I TRACKED HIM
THROUGH EDWARD'S GAME,

278
00:14:28,875 --> 00:14:31,666
AND WE'RE COMING UP ON HIM.

279
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,291
ARE YOU GUYS STANDING BY?

280
00:14:33,375 --> 00:14:34,375
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

281
00:14:34,458 --> 00:14:36,125
HE MADE IT MUCH
TOO EASY TO TRACE HIM.

282
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,708
THIS GUY'S TOO SMART FOR THAT.

283
00:14:37,791 --> 00:14:38,875
MAYBE IT'S A FALSE TRAIL.

284
00:14:38,958 --> 00:14:40,083
I MEAN, LOOK WHERE
WE'RE HEADING.

285
00:14:40,166 --> 00:14:42,083
WOULD HE BE IN A DUMP LIKE THAT?

286
00:14:42,166 --> 00:14:44,500
HOLD ON A MINUTE.

287
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,125
LISTEN TO ME.

288
00:14:46,208 --> 00:14:48,041
I HEARD ABOUT THIS PLACE
A LONG TIME AGO

289
00:14:48,125 --> 00:14:49,666
A KIND OF FLOATING SCRAP YARD

290
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:52,083
WHERE THEY LEAVE
WRECKED GATE PARTS,

291
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:54,166
ABANDONED SPACESHIPS,
AND SCRAP METAL.

292
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:56,458
PEOPLE MOVED IN

293
00:14:56,541 --> 00:14:58,125
AND STARTED LIVING THERE
SQUATTERS AND DRIFTERS.

294
00:14:58,208 --> 00:15:01,250
WHY THE HELL WOULD THEY WANT
TO LIVE THERE OF ALL PLACES?

295
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:02,333
THERE'S NO GOVERNMENT,

296
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:06,000
NO NATIONALITY,
NO TAXES, AND NO COPS.

297
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:08,208
THEY SEE IT AS TOTAL FREEDOM.

298
00:15:08,291 --> 00:15:09,583
YEAH, RIGHT.

299
00:15:09,666 --> 00:15:12,708
IT WOULD ALSO MAKE IT
A PERFECT PLACE TO HIDE OUT.

300
00:15:26,166 --> 00:15:31,250
REMEMBER, THIS COULD BE A TRAP,
A CONTINUATION OF THE GAME.

301
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:35,250
WHATEVER HAPPENS HAPPENS.

302
00:16:21,625 --> 00:16:23,666
LOOKS LIKE
THERE'S AIR IN HERE.

303
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:26,666
THEN THERE'S SOMEONE THERE.

304
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,791
[BEEPING]

305
00:16:28,875 --> 00:16:29,916
HMM?

306
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,541
HOW'S IT GOING, JET?

307
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:34,291
JONATHAN, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING OUT HERE?

308
00:16:34,375 --> 00:16:35,958
TRACKING YOU, OF COURSE.

309
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:37,208
THANKS FOR LEADING THE WAY.

310
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:39,583
YOU MEAN YOU'VE
BEEN FOLLOWING US?

311
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:40,416
WHAT FOR?

312
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:41,916
IT'S LIKE THIS.

313
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,125
I'VE GOT A SCORE TO SETTLE
WITH THE GUY YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

314
00:16:51,208 --> 00:16:54,250
[SCREAMING]

315
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,666
BYE-BYE.

316
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:07,666
[LAUGHING]

317
00:17:20,458 --> 00:17:23,250
OOH!

318
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:25,375
[CAT MEOWING]

319
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:30,666
WHAT THE?

320
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:36,166
[LAUGHING]

321
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:37,500
[GASPS]

322
00:17:37,583 --> 00:17:39,250
WHAT'S THAT?

323
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,708
UH, I

324
00:17:43,791 --> 00:17:45,458
[DOGS BARKING]

325
00:17:45,541 --> 00:17:49,458
WHAT THE HELL?

326
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:50,708
HUH?

327
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:56,708
[SNORING]

328
00:17:56,791 --> 00:17:58,333
WHAT'S THIS?

329
00:17:58,416 --> 00:18:02,458
[LAUGHING]

330
00:18:02,541 --> 00:18:05,000
WHAT'S GOING ON?

331
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:07,125
[LAUGHING]

332
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:20,708
HI.

333
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:24,083
PEACE TO THE WHOLE GALAXY
AND TO MY BANK ACCOUNT.

334
00:18:24,166 --> 00:18:25,208
LOVE, LOVE.

335
00:18:25,291 --> 00:18:27,791
DO YOU WANT ONE?

336
00:18:27,875 --> 00:18:30,791
AHH!

337
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:32,375
WOW! WHOA!

338
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:34,458
[LAUGHING]

339
00:18:42,958 --> 00:18:45,375
CHESS MASTER HEX,
I TAKE IT.

340
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:46,458
DON'T TRY ANYTHING.

341
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:47,583
UNDERSTAND?

342
00:18:47,666 --> 00:18:49,916
YOU BOTH, UH

343
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,458
WELL, COULD YOU BE JUST
A LITTLE QUIETER, PLEASE?

344
00:18:53,541 --> 00:18:54,916
HUH?

345
00:18:55,000 --> 00:19:00,750
OLD MAN... HAND IT OVER!

346
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,083
HEY, HOLD ON A MINUTE.

347
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:04,791
PRETENDING TO BE SENILE
WON'T GET YOU OUT OF THIS.

348
00:19:04,875 --> 00:19:05,916
WHO ARE YOU?

349
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,125
EITHER YOU GIVE ME
THE MONEY YOU TOOK,

350
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:09,750
OR I PUT A HOLE RIGHT
THROUGH YOUR BRAIN.

351
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,083
HEH HEH HEH!

352
00:19:11,166 --> 00:19:13,041
THAT'S QUITE
A LARGE PIPE THERE.

353
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:15,583
HEY, WHAT YOU DOING, HEX?

354
00:19:15,666 --> 00:19:17,375
OH, YOU GOT TO SEE THIS!

355
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:19,750
MY FIRST FORMIDABLE
OPPONENT IN AGES!

356
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:22,541
HE MUST BE SOME PLAYER
TO PIN YOU DOWN.

357
00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:23,541
WHAT'S YOUR NEXT MOVE?

358
00:19:23,625 --> 00:19:24,583
I DON'T KNOW.

359
00:19:24,666 --> 00:19:25,791
LET'S HAVE LUNCH FIRST.

360
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:28,458
YOU ATE LUNCH A FEW
MINUTES AGO, BLAST IT.

361
00:19:28,541 --> 00:19:30,083
REALLY? DID I LIKE IT?

362
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:32,208
WHO ARE THESE GUYS?

363
00:19:32,291 --> 00:19:35,416
DON'T KNOW,
BUT THIS ONE'S LOSING IT.

364
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:36,958
YOU LEAVE YOUR
BRAIN SOMEWHERE?

365
00:19:37,041 --> 00:19:40,208
YEAH, LIKE YOU CAN TALK,
YOU NUMBSKULL.

366
00:19:40,291 --> 00:19:44,500
ALL MY SAVINGS GONE.
I'LL NEVER GET IT BACK NOW.

367
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:46,416
DAMN IT. GODDAMN IT!

368
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:50,208
ANYONE, EVERYONE, YOU KNOW.

369
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,208
IT'S ALL A MISTAKE!

370
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:54,000
[SCREAMING]

371
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:58,375
[LAUGHING]

372
00:20:06,083 --> 00:20:07,583
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO WITH HIM?

373
00:20:07,666 --> 00:20:09,166
THE OLD DUFFER'S OUT OF TOUCH.

374
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:12,958
HE CAN'T RECALL YESTERDAY,
LET ALONE 50 YEARS AGO.

375
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:16,333
LUCKY FOR HIM,
HEX IS NO LONGER HERE.

376
00:20:16,416 --> 00:20:21,416
THERE'S NO ONE LEFT BUT AN OLD
MAN WHO LOVES TO PLAY GAMES.

377
00:20:23,541 --> 00:20:24,958
HEX WAS FURIOUS.

378
00:20:25,041 --> 00:20:27,541
HE WANTED REVENGE,
AND THIS IS HOW HE GOT IT.

379
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:29,458
HE SET UP THE STING
TO KICK IN 50 YEARS LATER

380
00:20:29,541 --> 00:20:31,000
WHEN THE GATE WAS PRE-SCHEDULED

381
00:20:31,083 --> 00:20:34,041
FOR ITS FIRST
AUTOMATIC TECH UPGRADE.

382
00:20:34,125 --> 00:20:35,458
IT WAS ALL PLANNED OUT.

383
00:20:35,541 --> 00:20:38,166
HE EVEN ARRANGED FOR HIS
OPERATIVES TO CARRY CHESS PIECES

384
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:41,541
TO LET YOU KNOW THAT HE HAD
FINALLY GOTTEN BACK AT YOU.

385
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:45,333
BUT 50 YEARS IS A LONG TIME.

386
00:20:45,416 --> 00:20:46,500
HEX GOT OLD.

387
00:20:46,583 --> 00:20:47,375
THEN HE GOT SENILE.

388
00:20:47,458 --> 00:20:48,625
HE COMPLETELY FORGOT ABOUT

389
00:20:48,708 --> 00:20:52,625
THE TRAPS THAT
HE HIMSELF HAD SET.

390
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:54,583
WELL, IT'S BETTER
FOR YOU THIS WAY.

391
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:56,416
YOU KNOW HE WON'T
EXPOSE YOU NOW.

392
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:59,000
YOUR DIRTY LITTLE SECRET
WILL REMAIN A SECRET.

393
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:00,625
HE CAN'T TELL ANYONE

394
00:21:00,708 --> 00:21:03,000
ABOUT THE DEFECTS
YOU BUILT INTO THE GATES.

395
00:21:03,083 --> 00:21:04,166
SO THAT'S IT, THEN.

396
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:05,791
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT IT.

397
00:21:05,875 --> 00:21:08,833
YOU JUST HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT US.

398
00:21:08,916 --> 00:21:10,166
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

399
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,625
MONEY? IS THAT IT?

400
00:21:11,708 --> 00:21:13,208
COME ON. SAY IT.

401
00:21:13,291 --> 00:21:17,916
WHAT'S YOUR PRICE TO KEEP FROM
LEAKING THIS THING TO THE PRESS?

402
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:21,166
JUST LEAVE THE OLD GUY ALONE.

403
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:22,625
CALL OFF THE BOUNTY HUNTERS.

404
00:21:22,708 --> 00:21:24,458
THAT'S ALL WE ASK.

405
00:21:24,541 --> 00:21:26,041
YOU SEE, ED WOULD BE UNHAPPY

406
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:29,541
IF SHE LOST
HER FAVORITE CHESS PARTNER,

407
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:34,250
AND WE WOULDN'T WANT THAT
TO HAPPEN, NOW, WOULD WE?

408
00:21:39,791 --> 00:21:41,875
ARE YOU PLAYING AGAIN?

409
00:21:41,958 --> 00:21:43,333
NOT AGAIN.

410
00:21:43,416 --> 00:21:44,666
ED'S STILL PLAYING.

411
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:49,125
YOU MEAN YOU'VE PLAYED
THE SAME GAME FOR A WEEK?

412
00:21:49,208 --> 00:21:50,291
MMHMM.

413
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:51,541
I SEE.

414
00:21:51,625 --> 00:21:54,500
WELL, GOOD LUCK, ED.

415
00:21:56,583 --> 00:21:59,375
YO, NEWBY, YOU'RE
IN A GOOD MOOD TODAY.

416
00:21:59,458 --> 00:22:00,708
HOWDY THERE, GUYS.

417
00:22:00,791 --> 00:22:02,666
HE'S AN EASYGOING
DUDE, AIN'T HE?

418
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:04,208
SURE IS, ANTONIO.

419
00:22:04,291 --> 00:22:05,458
NICE FELLA.

420
00:22:05,541 --> 00:22:07,500
CHECKMATE.

421
00:22:07,583 --> 00:22:10,625
CHECKMATE.

422
00:22:10,708 --> 00:22:14,750
AAH!

423
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:20,166
HE GOT ME!

424
00:22:26,708 --> 00:22:28,666
[CHIRPING]

425
00:22:41,458 --> 00:22:43,666
[SQUAWKING]

426
00:24:26,166 --> 00:24:28,708
LOVE IS TO BELIEVE
IN EVERYTHING.

427
00:24:28,791 --> 00:24:30,416
WAIT A MINUTE.
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

428
00:24:30,500 --> 00:24:32,416
LOVE IS THE HEART
THAT GIVES TO ALL.

429
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:34,666
COME ON! THAT'S WHAT
THE STORY'S ABOUT!

430
00:24:34,750 --> 00:24:37,166
LOVE IS THE HEART
THAT ACCEPTS EVERYTHING.

431
00:24:37,250 --> 00:24:38,958
YOU KNOW I'M NOT BUYING THIS.

432
00:24:39,041 --> 00:24:40,666
WHITNEY,
YOU LOVE ME THAT MUCH.

433
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:43,291
YOU REALLY CAN'T TRUST
THE PREVIEWS ON THIS SHOW.

434
00:24:43,375 --> 00:24:45,875
A ROMANTIC LOVE STORY
FOR ALL YOU LOVERS.

435
00:24:45,958 --> 00:24:48,958
NEXT EPISODE
MY FUNNY VALENTINE.

436
00:24:49,041 --> 00:24:50,166
IT'S GOTTA BE A LIE.

437
00:24:50,250 --> 00:24:52,208
YEAH.
SHE'S MAKING IT UP.

